OL,4,Cdeath was a 'shambles', inquest told
OL,6,FHe said he was about to give
OL,7,Fintravenous drugs to Mr Townsend,
OL,8,Fbecause nobody else seemed to be doing
OL,9,Fit, when a steward asked him to "move
OL,10,Faway".
OL,12,FDr Stones said it was one of the worst
OL,13,Fpre-hospital critical care scenarios
OL,14,Fthat he had witnessed, adding it was
OL,15,F"just awful".
OL,17,FMr Stones also told the inquest that
OL,18,Fthere was a ten minute wait for
OL,19,Ffurther help.
